<ITEM><PB N="307" REF="362"> Antilopes; thirteen different &s;pecies of them, vi. 393. The common Antilope de&s;cribed, 412. Indian Antilopes have more &s;pirit than tho&s;e of other countries, 414. n. All the different kinds of them found in A&s;ia and Africa, 415. Diffi|culty of arranging them, 416. The larger kinds more com|mon in Africa than India, 422. The eyes of tho&s;e in the neighbourhood of Alexandria &s;o beautiful, that they are &s;po|ken of figuratively in prai&s;ing the eyes of the ladies, 423. n. The different kinds particularly de&s;cribed, vii. 1. <HI>et &s;eq.</HI></ITEM>
