<HI>ib.</HI> Their hor&s;es the mo&s;t beautiful, iii. 357. Their de|&s;cent, way in which they are treated, &s;wiftne&s;s, &amp;c. 365. <HI>et &s;eq.</HI> Surmount many difficulties by means of their camels, vi. 128. Fir&s;t took notice of the mu&s;k, vii. 45.</ITEM>
