<ITEM>Brain cannot be the fountain of &s;en&s;ation, iv. 173. Is only a &s;pecies of mucilage, and hardly organized, 174. Is an organ of &s;ecretion and nutrition, 175. Is not proportionally larger in man than other animals, 176. Ought not to be regarded as an organic part of the nervous &s;y&s;tem, 177. Why the compre&s;&s;ion of it de&s;troys &s;en&s;ation, <HI>ib.</HI> Facts which &s;hew that the brain is not the organ of &s;en&s;ation, <HI>ib.</HI></ITEM>
